summary: ok one thing has been driving me crazy. i don't think i fully understood the significance of the line, "you go too fast for me,...
question: ok one thing has been driving me crazy. i don't think i fully understood the significance of the line, "you go too fast for me, crowley." what does it mean exactly?
answer: I read it as fear, pretty much- Aziraphale is afraid of how much he loves Crowley enjoys Crowley’s company. He just brought him a thermos of holy water so he wouldn’t do something stupid/dangerous to get it. Their relationship has obviously gone far beyond a simple arrangement to prevent redundancy in their respective job responsibilities, and I feel like that was Aziraphale’s “oh shit” moment.

Okay, so a couple weeks ago, I posted that short comic of Aziraphale using a megaphone to tell people to get out of his bookshop. In the comic, I included Aziraphale’s angel wing mug on his desk.

I noticed that multiple people reblogging it and theorising that Crowley gave Aziraphale the mug as a joke, but Aziraphale not only kept it, he uses it as his speciality cocoa mug, and I just want to say that I accept your headcanons.

summary:
the one thing that i really respect about the Good Omens adaptation is how faithful it stayed to the book. 
sure there were...
body:
the one thing that i really respect about the Good Omens adaptation is how faithful it stayed to the book.

sure there were changes here and there but it was still just how everyone imagined it but better, no matter how ridiculous that seems on screen.

like in the final confrontation, for example, i always imagined the kids confronting the four horsemen of the fucking apocalypse, destroying them one by one while aziraphale, crowley, shadwell, madam tracey, newt, and anathema, just stood there uselessly, watching

and what did the adaptation give me? exactly fucking that. no bullshitting, no needless pandering, just straight up honest to god recreation on screen

and i am SO immensely grateful to it for that

summary: So I just started Good Omens and
body:
So I just started Good Omens and

  • David Tennant is still a gift from God
  • Crowley is a Queen stan I’m screaming!!!!
  • I will be dancing to every Queen song that starts playing unless restrained.
  • The anti-Christ is precious and please let him bring about good (that is a sentence I hope I’ll be forgiven for)
  • Every time I see Gabriel all I can think is “John Hamm Solo”
  • David Tennant dressed as a nanny
  • If Mozart is in Hell, where are Freddie Mercury and John Lennon?
  • George Harrison???
  • (Edit: thanks for reminding me Beethoven and Bach are in Heaven)
